== 1. Graduate Analyst / Research Associate

=== Hierarchy Level
Entry-level position, typically 0-2 years of experience

=== Key Activities and Responsibilities
- *Data Collection & Processing*: Gathering financial statements, company announcements, broker reports, and industry data
- *Financial Modelling*: Building and maintaining financial models (DCF, comparable company analysis, precedent transactions)
- *Company Monitoring*: Tracking portfolio companies and coverage universe, flagging material developments
- *Meeting Support*: Preparing briefing materials for company meetings, attending alongside senior analysts
- *Industry Research*: Compiling industry reports, competitive landscape analysis, and thematic research
- *Administrative Support*: Maintaining research databases, updating sector dashboards, preparing presentation materials

=== Required Skills

*Technical:*
- Financial statement analysis and accounting knowledge
- Excel modelling (three-statement models, DCF, sensitivity analysis)
- Bloomberg/FactSet/Capital IQ proficiency
- Understanding of valuation methodologies
- Basic knowledge of equity markets and investment concepts

*Interpersonal:*
- Strong written communication for research notes
- Attention to detail and accuracy
- Ability to synthesise large amounts of information
- Time management across multiple tasks
- Willingness to learn and take feedback

*Regulatory:*
- Understanding of continuous disclosure obligations (ASX Listing Rules)
- Awareness of insider trading restrictions
- Familiarity with fair dealing and information barriers

=== Typical Work Modes

*Analytical Work (60-70%):*
- Building financial models at desk
- Reading annual reports, broker research, industry publications
- Analysing company announcements and market data
- Preparing research summaries and updates

*Meetings (20-25%):*
- Company management meetings (observing, note-taking)
- Internal team meetings and research discussions
- Training sessions and professional development

*Presentations (5-10%):*
- Presenting findings to senior analysts
- Summarising company results or industry developments
- Contributing to portfolio review meetings

*Other (5-10%):*
- Industry conferences and site visits
- Networking with brokers and company IR teams
- Administrative tasks and database maintenance

=== A Day in the Life

*7:30am - 8:30am*: Review overnight market movements, read ASX announcements from portfolio companies, scan broker research for coverage universe. Prepare morning briefing notes on any material developments.

*8:30am - 9:00am*: Morning team meeting – discuss market developments, upcoming company meetings, research priorities. Senior analyst assigns tasks for the day: update model for upcoming earnings, prepare briefing pack for tomorrow's management meeting.

*9:00am - 12:00pm*: Deep work session. Update three-statement model for BHP ahead of results next week. Cross-reference guidance from recent investor presentations, update commodity price assumptions, run sensitivity analysis on iron ore prices. Send draft model to senior analyst for review.

*12:00pm - 1:00pm*: Attend company management meeting via video conference with Wesfarmers IR team. Senior analyst leads questioning on Bunnings performance and Kmart strategy. Take detailed notes, capture key metrics and forward guidance.

*1:00pm - 2:00pm*: Lunch while reading through Macquarie's latest materials sector report. Flag interesting points on lithium supply dynamics for discussion with team.

*2:00pm - 3:30pm*: Write up meeting notes from Wesfarmers call. Summarise key takeaways, compare management commentary to model assumptions, flag any changes to investment thesis. Share notes with Portfolio Manager and team.

*3:30pm - 5:00pm*: Research request from Portfolio Manager: "Quick view on Aristocrat's new slot machine launch – material to thesis?" Scan industry publications, check competitor releases, review broker notes. Draft 1-page summary with initial assessment.

*5:00pm - 6:00pm*: Attend internal research presentation by Healthcare analyst covering CSL's new plasma collection strategy. Participate in Q&A, learn about team's research process.

*6:00pm onwards*: Finish updating sector dashboard with latest company announcements. Prepare tomorrow's priority list based on upcoming earnings releases. Most days leave by 6:30-7:00pm, though later during reporting season.

=== Career Progression Pathways
- *2-4 years*: Analyst → Senior Analyst (take ownership of small-cap coverage)
- *4-7 years*: Senior Analyst → Sector Analyst (lead coverage of sector)
- *7-10+ years*: Sector Analyst → Portfolio Manager or Head of Research

*Alternative paths:*
- Move to buy-side research at hedge fund (higher intensity, potentially higher compensation)
- Transition to corporate finance/strategy at operating company
- Join sell-side research at investment bank or broker
- Move to investor relations at listed company

