*9:30am - 11:00am*: Deep work on upcoming investment idea for Investment Committee. You've been building conviction on Domino's Pizza – franchise model provides defensive growth, digital platform driving market share gains, valuation reasonable relative to QSR peers. Refine DCF model, complete peer benchmarking analysis across global QSR franchise businesses.

*11:00am - 12:00pm*: Company meeting with Cochlear management via video. You lead questioning on competitor dynamics in cochlear implant market, probe on recent FDA approval delays, discuss R&D pipeline. Build rapport with CFO for future calls.

*12:00pm - 1:00pm*: Lunch with sell-side analyst from Morgans who covers retail. Discuss foot traffic trends in shopping centres, online penetration across categories, thoughts on upcoming Christmas trading. Useful colour for multiple holdings.

*1:00pm - 2:00pm*: Write up Cochlear meeting notes. Key takeaway: FDA approval timeline unchanged despite recent media speculation, new product launch on track for FY26. No change to thesis, remain comfortable with position.

*2:00pm - 4:00pm*: Continue work on Domino's investment paper. Write investment thesis section: 1) structural growth in food delivery penetration, 2) technology platform moat, 3) franchise model with high ROIC, 4) experienced management team. Include key risks: competition from Uber Eats aggregation, franchise profitability pressure, international market execution.

