*Interpersonal:*
- Strong professional networks (company management, sell-side, industry experts)
- Excellent written communication for investment papers
- Confident oral presentation skills for Investment Committee
- Mentoring and coaching abilities
- Influencing portfolio managers and challenging consensus views

*Regulatory:*
- Deep understanding of corporate governance issues
- Expert knowledge of disclosure obligations and market conduct
- Sophisticated understanding of MNPI and information barriers
- Awareness of proxy voting and stewardship responsibilities

=== Typical Work Modes

*Analytical Work (45-55%):*
- Complex company and industry analysis
- Developing differentiated investment views
- Writing detailed research reports and investment papers
- Strategic thinking about portfolio positioning

*Meetings (30-35%):*
